  schema:name "Poaceae" ;
  schema:description "Grass family — ~780 genera, ~12,000 species (fifth-largest angiosperm family). Diagnostic hollow culm stems, ligule at leaf-sheath junction, spikelet inflorescence, caryopsis (grain) fruit, wind pollination. Most economically important plant family; covers ~40% of Earth's land surface." ;
